\par YM:\tab Yes.
\par NL:\tab How did you know him?
\par YM:\tab Him, I knew only through official channels, like, I was a member of the board at the Zionist, World Zionist Organization of the }{\i\fs24 Keren Kayemet}{\fs24 , the }{\i\fs24 Keren Ha'yesod}{\fs24 , and we used 
to meet in good times, you know, in '36, '37,
\par NL:\tab I see.
\par YM:\tab And we spoke about it that the danger is very great, and this and that, and then I had the troubles with, as a Czechoslovakian citizen to remain in Hungary and work in Hungary because they, the H
ungarian government, emulated so to say, the permission given to me earlier to work in Hungary, so I was in and out and tried to get through Yugoslavia, contacts with England, where I really went for a, an audition to the Duke's Place Temple and so on, so
 I really...
\par NL:\tab And did he help you?
\par YM:\tab No.
\par NL:\tab He didn't help you, but you tried to get some help from him?
\par YM:\tab No, not from him.
\par NL:\tab Oh.
\par YM:\tab I never, I never.
\par NL:\tab Oh.
\par YM:\tab You know, he was one of the, one of the board members, one of the boys, so to say.
